				\begin{document}$$\gg$$\end{document}≫ 0) corresponding to Head Casts, and a monoactive state (rate(B1) ≫ 0, rate(B2) ≃ 0) corresponding to Hunches. The two behaviors can also be distinguished by the single scalar rate(B2)/rate(B1), which is large for Head Casts and small for Hunches. This ratio is sometimes plotted instead of the discrete category.

